node.text: I’m raising my voice alongside Mikre to tell the story of a young girl’s emancipation and empowerment in Mikre’s own words. She was 12 years old when she was forced to marry a man more than twice her age. Mikre wasn’t interested in that kind of arithmetic and figured out how to solve the problem. In honor of International #dayofthegirl on October 11th, join me and @careorg and tell Congress to put women and girls like Mikre at the center of a COVID19 response. Link in bio.

node.text: It isn’t easy to take care of yourself, and when the pressure is on you, it takes real strength to step back and be okay with the feeling of “letting others down” and “letting yourself down”. I admire Simone Biles - and I encourage you all- especially during these times- to be okay when YOU get the “twisties” or the “yips”- terms used in sports but I think that can be applied to all areas of life. One of the most difficult things to do as we go through the process of living is to go through the ups and downs and work through the complicated nature of our own minds. Support others and support yourself and be okay with stepping back sometimes when you have the “twisties.” Link to article about the meaning in bio
